                <h1>"Does a DUI Show Up on Background Checks Without Conviction?"</h1>
                <p>A DUI charge may appear on a background check even if you were not convicted. Arrest records generally remain public, and employers often see them. However, the results can vary based on the type of background check conducted and local laws. It's crucial to understand your rights and report any discrepancies during job applications.</p>
